{
  "sheet_file": "jobide.png",
  "symbol_size": 160,
  "cols": 10,
  "rows": 3,
  "writing_mode": "circular_clockwise_4",
  "spacing": { "x": 10, "y": 10 },
  "trim": { "left": 0, "right": 0, "top": 0, "bottom": 0 },
  "overlay": {
    "enabled": true,
    "roots": ["i", "u", "e", "a", "o", "'"],
    "blockers": [],
    "offset_x": 0,
    "offset_y": 0
  },
  "tokenizer": { "separator": " " },
  "description": "Jobid'e language character symbols",
  "notes": "Silencio en [0,0]. 6 vocales (i,u,e,a,o,') se sobreponen sobre consonante o silencio. Las mismas vocales repetidas en posiciones [0,7]-[1,1] son las FORMAS CONSONANTICAS (ic,uc,ec,ac,oc). La silaba es siempre consonante+vocal. La vocal final apostrofe puede omitirse en transliteracion. La palabra 'jobid'e' en realidad es 'jobid'e'' con 4 silabas: jo bi d' e'. Separador en ultima posicion.",
  "root_mapping": {
    "_": [0, 0],
    "i":    [0, 1],
    "u":    [0, 2],
    "e":    [0, 3],
    "a":    [0, 4],
    "o":    [0, 5],
    "'":    [0, 6],
    "ic":   [0, 7],
    "uc":   [0, 8],
    "ec":   [0, 9],
    "ac":   [1, 0],
    "oc":   [1, 1],
    "d":    [1, 2],
    "t":    [1, 3],
    "s":    [1, 4],
    "l":    [1, 5],
    "n":    [1, 6],
    "m":    [1, 7],
    "j":    [1, 8],
    "g":    [1, 9],
    "b":    [2, 0],
    "f":    [2, 1],
    "y":    [2, 2],
    "?":    [2, 3],
    " ":    [2, 4]
  }
}
